title: ComicPirates Weeklies Index (CPWI) (2012-04 - 2015-02) (N=116k)
description:
CONTAINS:       Plaintext contents listings covering all Weeklies (and Monthlies and
                Annuals) posted from TPB accounts <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipj" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipj</a>
                and <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipjolly" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/user/shipjolly</a>  as well as from KAT
                account "shipjolly", corresponding to well above 90% of all English
                comics releases that went through the "official" channels, plus a
                smattering of non-English ones, during the stated period.

DETAILS:        First = 2012-04-11   |   Last = 2015-02-25   |   Count = 116,174

FORMATTING:     The original data stems directly from the contents of the metadata
                files (see  <a href=" https://thepiratebay.se/torrent/11735863" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> https://thepiratebay.se/torrent/11735863</a>   ), and was
                automatically processed into the following standardized format.

   |t>14-09-10 0000|s> 912,274,022|n>Spacehawk (2012) (Digital) (Bean-Empire).cbz

   t(imestamp)  two digits each for year, month, day, hour, minute of release. The
                last two are always 00, functioning only as placeholders here.
   (file)s(ize) in bytes, formatted for improved legibility. Fixed-width field with
                a 10-gigabyte maximum, which should suffice for a while yet!
   (file)n(ame) including filetype extension.

ORGANIZATION:   The three contained files are each sorted by a combination of two
                of the three - specifically, by name then time (filename suffix "by
                nt"), by size then name ("by sn"), and by time then name ("by tn").

LIVE VERSION:  <a href=" http://gesserit.000space.com/www/both" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://gesserit.000space.com/www/both</a>
